data.description: Motivated Seller willing to negotiate has multiple reports on the house installing a new hvac and new hot water heater.   Turn of the century farmhouse, metal roof, with updated section renovated approximately 1960.  4 bedrooms 2 bathrooms historic farm house on over an acre with a workshop that was once used as a deer cooler which would be a fabulous space for an art studio, a pet grooming shop, or even that small online business you are looking to start. The barn also has a pole barn parking for two or more vehicles an office and a 2 car carport a roll up door area great for a workshop and has electric! We have a home Inspection completed by the fabulous brickkicker of Athens and the report is available. Pest control has been out NO present or past termite activity in this 1904 home. The roof has been inspected by an insured roofing contractor no moisture or leaks report available. Home is estimated as being built in 1904 but tax records state 1960 after first renovation. This home has lots of storage areas and huge closet spaces. New luxury vinyl plank throughout the main floor and bathrooms, new carpet in bedrooms and upstairs, new paint, new countertops in kitchen. Two fireplaces in the home, plenty of large trees providing shade and privacy around the home. The home is close to Victoria Bryant State Park and Golf Course, 2 miles from I85 access and 15 minutes from Lake Hartwell. Lots of potential with this updated country farmhouse.
